%20in%20federal%20court%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20week%20over%20the%20new%20blacklist%2C%20and%20industry%20execs%20have%20spent%20months%20trading%20barbs%20via%20social%20media%2C%20speeches%2C%20and%20email%20blasts%20that%20reached%20thousands%20of%20agents%20across%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20back-and-forth%20leaves%20homebuyers%20and%20sellers%20in%20a%20weird%20spot.%20I've%20spent%20months%20talking%20to%20people%20around%20the%20industry%20about%20the%20hidden%20listings%20issue%2C%20and%20I'm%20left%20with%20one%20big%20conclusion%3A%20If%20you%20decide%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbad-real-estate-agents-realtors-homebuyers-sellers-housing-market-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehire%20an%20agent%3C%2Fa%3E%20(which%20most%20people%20do)%2C%20you%20should%20go%20into%20that%20relationship%20with%20open%20eyes.%20The%20rules%20of%20the%20game%20are%20changing.%20Consumers%20need%20to%20make%20sure%20they%20know%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhomebuyers-real-estate-revolution-nar-lawsuits-new-rules-realtors-agents-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexactly%20what%20they're%20getting%20from%20their%20agents%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20how%20much%20they'll%20be%20paying%20for%20those%20services.%20Buyers'%20agents%20should%20also%20be%20able%20to%20explain%20how%20they'll%20navigate%20a%20shifting%20landscape%20in%20which%20some%20listings%20may%20become%20harder%20to%20find.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBig%20companies%20are%20squabbling%20because%20they%20need%20your%20clicks%2C%20your%20home%20listings%2C%20and%2C%20ultimately%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-agents-lawsuits-buy-sell-homes-forever-housing-market-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecommission%20checks%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20flow%20from%20your%20deal.%20Whether%20you're%20a%20buyer%20or%20seller%2C%20your%20business%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhouse-prices-market-set-worst-year-decades-meredith-whitney-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eespecially%20valuable%20right%20now%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20can%20be%20daunting%2C%20but%20the%20upheaval%20may%20be%20advantageous%20if%20you%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhomebuyers-sellers-realtor-agent-commissions-saving-rule-changes-lawsuit-settlement-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplay%20your%20next%20home%20transaction%20correctly%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20real%20estate%20company%20has%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnational-association-realtors-rules-commissions-zillow-home-search-pocket-listings-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehuge%20financial%20stake%20in%20this%20war%20over%20listings%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Zillow's%20new%20policy%20is%20an%20attempt%20to%20stem%20the%20rising%20tide%20of%20%26quot%3Bexclusive%20inventory%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20homes%20marketed%20outside%20the%20multiple%20listing%20services%2C%20the%20formal%20name%20for%20the%20more%20than%20500%20local%20databases%20that%20distribute%20listings%20among%20fellow%20agents%2C%20big%20brokerages%2C%20and%20the%20popular%20search%20portals.%20Instead%20of%20being%20entered%20into%20the%20MLS%2C%20these%20%26quot%3Bhidden%26quot%3B%20houses%20are%20shared%20among%20agents%20who%20belong%20to%20the%20same%20brokerage%2C%20swapped%20in%20clubby%20groups%20known%20as%20private%20listing%20networks%2C%20or%20posted%20exclusively%20on%20one%20brokerage's%20website%20without%20being%20distributed%20more%20widely.%20The%20leader%20of%20the%20push%20toward%20this%20walled-garden%20approach%20is%20Compass%2C%20which%20maintains%20its%20own%20trove%20of%20thousands%20of%20homes%20that%20you%20can%20only%20see%20by%20working%20with%20one%20of%20their%20agents.%20But%20it's%20far%20from%20the%20only%20company%20doing%20this%20%E2%80%94%20other%20major%20players%2C%20such%20as%20Howard%20Hanna%2C%20are%20increasingly%20leaning%20on%20hidden%20listings.%20Still%20others%20have%20threatened%20that%20they%20could%20do%20the%20same%20if%20the%20market%20fractures%20further.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZillow%20really%20doesn't%20like%20this%20shift.%20The%20company%20depends%20on%20selling%20leads%20tied%20to%20the%20mountain%20of%20listings%20in%20its%20portal%3A%20When%20you%20signal%20your%20interest%20in%20a%20property%20on%20its%20website%2C%20Zillow%20will%20typically%20pass%20along%20your%20contact%20info%20to%20an%20agent%20who%20pays%20a%20fee%20to%20the%20site%20%E2%80%94%20not%20the%20agent%20who%20actually%20listed%20the%20house%20for%20sale.%20If%20the%20spigot%20of%20home%20listings%20gets%20cut%20off%2C%20search%20portals%20like%20Zillow%20are%20in%20trouble.%20Beyond%20self-interest%2C%20the%20company%20says%20it's%20also%20fighting%20for%20something%20far%20more%20noble%3A%20a%20fair%20and%20transparent%20housing%20market%2C%20in%20which%20listings%20are%20readily%20available%20for%20everyone%20to%20see.%20Buyers%20just%20want%20to%20see%20all%20the%20houses%20out%20there%2C%20Zillow%20execs%20say%2C%20and%20sellers%20can%20draw%20out%20the%20best%20offers%20when%20their%20homes%20get%20maximum%20exposure.%20Plenty%20of%20agents%20around%20the%20industry%20resent%20Zillow%20for%20the%20power%20it%20wields%2C%20but%20even%20some%20who%20have%20beef%20with%20the%20search%20giant%20have%20told%20me%20they%20agree%20with%20its%20basic%20point%3A%20A%20wide-open%20market%20is%20best%20for%20consumers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKirk%20Simmon%2C%20a%2020-year%20veteran%20agent%20in%20the%20suburbs%20of%20Philadelphia%2C%20touts%20what%20he%20calls%20a%20%26quot%3Bpublic%20inclusive%26quot%3B%20approach%20%E2%80%94%20a%20play%20on%20Compass's%20%26quot%3BPrivate%20Exclusive%26quot%3B%20listings%2C%20which%20are%20distributed%20internally%20among%20Compass%20agents%20and%20their%20clients.%20For%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20people%20%E2%80%94%20except%2C%20maybe%2C%20A-list%20celebrities%20or%20those%20who%20desire%20true%20privacy%20%E2%80%94%20Simmon%20advises%20sharing%20a%20home%20listing%20as%20widely%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhy%20would%20you%20ever%20sell%20your%20house%20without%20the%20public%20knowing%20and%20everybody%20being%20included%3F%26quot%3B%20Simmon%20tells%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDick%20Selzer%2C%20the%20owner%20and%20general%20manager%20of%20a%20Re%2FMax-affiliated%20brokerage%20in%20northern%20California%2C%20agrees.%20%26quot%3BCandidly%2C%20I%20hate%20to%20come%20to%20the%20aid%20of%20Zillow%20because%20I%20don't%20particularly%20like%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Selzer%20tells%20me.%20But%2C%20he%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BMy%20job%20is%20not%20to%20be%20happy%20with%20Zillow.%20My%20job%20is%20to%20do%20the%20best%20I%20can%20for%20my%20client.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20gotten%20a%20similar%20message%20from%20Compass%20agents%20on%20the%20opposite%20side%20of%20the%20aisle%2C%20who%20say%20they'll%20stick%20with%20their%20marketing%20strategy%20despite%20Zillow's%20new%20rule.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20going%20to%20let%20them%20bully%20me%20into%20doing%20things%20that%20are%20detrimental%20to%20my%20clients%2C%26quot%3B%20Jennifer%20Knoll%2C%20a%20Compass%20agent%20in%20the%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20area%2C%20told%20me%20recently%2C%20emphasizing%20that%20she%20always%20has%20clear%20discussions%20with%20her%20clients%20about%20their%20marketing%20plans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompass%20says%20the%20search%20portal's%20new%20policy%20is%20just%20an%20attempt%20to%20protect%20its%20market%20dominance.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frobert-reffkin-compass-ceo-real-estate-career-rise-job-history-2021-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERobert%20Reffkin%2C%20Compass's%20CEO%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20argues%20that%20sellers%20benefit%20from%20testing%20their%20home%20listings%20with%20a%20limited%20audience%20before%20blasting%20them%20out%20more%20widely.%20The%20Compass%20website%2C%20unlike%20Zillow%2C%20Realtor.com%2C%20or%20any%20of%20the%20other%20big%20search%20websites%2C%20doesn't%20track%20price%20cuts%20or%20show%20how%20long%20a%20house%20has%20been%20sitting%20on%20the%20market%2C%20information%20that%20Reffkin%20says%20harms%20sellers.%20Compass%20can%20also%20monetize%20leads%20through%20its%20own%20website%20rather%20than%20handing%20those%20opportunities%20to%20a%20portal%20like%20Zillow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20thing%20consumers%20need%20to%20know%20is%20that%20they%20can%20%E2%80%94%20and%20should%20%E2%80%94%20be%20part%20of%20this%20conversation.%20Sellers%20should%20know%20exactly%20how%20their%20agent%20plans%20to%20market%20their%20home%2C%20and%20why%20they're%20doing%20what%20they're%20doing.%20Some%20of%20this%20comes%20down%20to%20just%20reading%20the%20forms.%20One%20of%20Compass's%20disclosure%20forms%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20warns%20sellers%20that%20listing%20homes%20off%20the%20MLS%20may%20%26quot%3Breduce%26quot%3B%20the%20number%20of%20potential%20buyers%20who%20learn%20about%20the%20property%2C%20the%20number%20of%20offers%2C%20and%20ultimately%2C%20the%20sale%20price%20(94%25%20of%20Compass's%20listings%20last%20year%20eventually%20sold%20via%20the%20MLS%2C%20the%20company%20says%2C%20even%20though%20many%20were%20initially%20marketed%20in%20Compass's%20internal%20database).%20The%20form%20also%20warns%20sellers%20of%20the%20chance%20that%20their%20house%20won't%20show%20up%20on%20Zillow%20if%20the%20listing's%20advertisements%20run%20afoul%20of%20the%20search%20giant's%20new%20policy.%20A%20Compass%20spokesperson%20said%20in%20an%20email%20that%20while%20the%20company's%20research%20shows%20that%20consumers%20benefit%20from%20pre-marketing%2C%20the%20disclosure%20form%20reflects%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20company%20cannot%20guarantee%20results.%20One%20thing%20is%20clear%3A%20Sellers%20should%20know%20the%20trade-offs%20baked%20into%20any%20marketing%20plan%20for%20their%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20buyers%2C%20a%20whole%20%3Cem%3Eother%3C%2Fem%3E%20set%20of%20rules%20from%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnational-association-realtors-lawsuit-settlement-housing-market-homebuying-agents-commissions-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emassive%20legal%20settlement%3C%2Fa%3E%20against%20the%20real%20estate%20industry%20last%20year%20dictate%20that%20before%20you%20so%20much%20as%20step%20into%20a%20house%20with%20an%20agent%20as%20your%20guide%2C%20you%20have%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-homebuying-rule-sign-buyer-representation-agreement-realtors-lawsuit-settlement-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esign%20an%20agreement%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20outlines%20the%20terms%20of%20the%20agent's%20services%20and%20how%20much%20they%20expect%20to%20be%20paid.%20Buyers%20can%20no%20longer%20coast%20on%20the%20assumption%20that%20their%20agents'%20services%20are%20free%2C%20and%20they%20should%20make%20sure%20they're%20getting%20their%20money's%20worth.%20And%20though%20many%20homes%20are%20available%20in%20the%20major%20search%20portals%20these%20days%2C%20buyers%20have%20always%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-agents-realtors-reckoning-housing-market-home-sales-slow-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erelied%20upon%20agents%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20dig%20up%20the%20houses%20that%20can't%20be%20found%20online.%20That's%20not%20changing%20anytime%20soon%2C%20especially%20in%20markets%20that%20are%20still%20starved%20for%20available%20inventory.%20One%20Zillow%20economist%20recently%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%2C%20after%20a%20tumultuous%20home%20search%20this%20spring%2C%20he%20eventually%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fzillow-economist-homebuying-difficulties-raleigh-durham-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epurchased%20a%20home%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20had%20not%20been%20officially%20listed%20for%20sale%20%E2%80%94%20his%20agent%20had%20heard%20of%20a%20homeowner%20who%20could%20be%20prompted%20to%20sell%20for%20the%20right%20offer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAgain%2C%20you%20probably%20won't%20notice%20anything%20different%20on%20Zillow%20or%20any%20of%20the%20other%20popular%20search%20portals%20in%20the%20coming%20weeks.%20Zillow%20has%20spent%20the%20past%20month%20warning%20agents%20whose%20home%20advertisements%20violate%20its%20new%20rules%2C%20and%20while%20the%20company%20won't%20say%20exactly%20how%20many%20listings%20it's%20flagged%20so%20far%2C%20Errol%20Samuelson%2C%20Zillow's%20chief%20industry%20development%20officer%2C%20said%20in%20an%20email%20statement%20that%20the%20company%20expects%20%26quot%3Bonly%20a%20small%20number%20of%20for-sale%20listings%20will%20be%20affected.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEveryone%20involved%20in%20this%20fight%20is%20scrambling%20to%20protect%20their%20slice%20of%20the%20pie.%20Savvy%20consumers%20should%20have%20no%20illusions%20about%20where%20they%20stand%20in%20this%20ecosystem.%20This%20may%20be%20happening%20out%20of%20sight%2C%20but%20buyers%20and%20sellers%20alike%20lose%20if%20they%20keep%20it%20out%20of%20mind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fjames-rodriguez%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EJames%20Rodriguez%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20reporter%20on%20Business%20Insider's%20Discourse%20team.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fzillow-ban-blacklist-real-estate-listings-what-homebuyers-can-do-2025-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1751270821000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F685efc4c3d5881a51c1c4c09%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fzillow-ban-blacklist-real-estate-listings-what-homebuyers-can