attice%2C%20a%20human-resources%20software%20startup%20last%20valued%20at%20%243%20billion%2C%20for%20over%20eight%20years%20before%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjack-altman-steps-down-ceo-cofounder-lattice-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estepping%20down%20as%20its%20CEO%20last%20year%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20has%20since%20launched%20Alt%20Capital%2C%20an%20early-stage%20venture%20firm%20that%20has%20invested%20in%20AI%20and%20nuclear%20energy%20companies.%20In%20February%202024%2C%20the%20firm%20raised%20a%20%24150%20million%20fund%20to%20invest%20in%20seed%20and%20Series%20A%20startups.%20Alt%20Capital%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20podcast%2C%20Altman%20said%20that%20picking%20good%20board%20members%20is%20crucial%20because%20founders%20end%20up%20making%20%26quot%3Bhigh-stakes%26quot%3B%20decisions%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20turns%20out%20that%20what%20you're%20picking%20is%20somebody%20who's%20going%20to%20be%20there%20with%20you%20longer%20than%20most%20of%20your%20employees%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20going%20to%20talk%20to%20them%20about%20stuff%20that%20you're%20not%20going%20to%20talk%20to%20your%20employees%20about%20because%20you%20can't.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAltman%20added%20that%20picking%20investors%20you%20like%20doesn't%20matter%20as%20much%20in%20the%20seed%20stage%2C%20but%20it%20becomes%20important%20once%20companies%20create%20boards%20of%20directors.%20According%20to%20PitchBook%2C%20he%20is%20on%20the%20boards%20of%20two%20startups%3A%20WorkRamp%20and%20Verifiable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGetting%20board%20composition%20right%20is%20a%20heavily%20discussed%20topic%20in%20Silicon%20Valley.%20Investors%20often%20find%20themselves%20being%20rated%20on%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fis-benchmark-capital-founder-friendly-2019-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efounder%20friendliness%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20an%20approach%20that%20prioritizes%20the%20founder's%20vision%20and%20expertise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeta's%20CEO%2C%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%2C%20has%20said%20a%20lack%20of%20technical%20chops%20in%20board%20leadership%20was%20one%20of%20the%20first%20things%20he%20noticed%20when%20he%20went%20to%20Silicon%20Valley%2C%20and%20it%20was%20among%20the%20things%20he%20wanted%20to%20do%20differently%20at%20Meta.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20CEO%20wasn't%20technical%2C%20the%20board%20of%20directors%20had%20no%20one%20technical%20on%20it%2C%20they%20had%20like%20one%20dude%20on%20the%20management%20team%20who%20was%20the%20head%20of%20engineering%20who%20was%20technical%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20of%20his%20early%20observations%2C%20in%20an%20interview%20last%20year.%20%26quot%3BAlright%2C%20if%20that's%20your%20team%2C%20then%20you're%20not%20a%20technology%20company.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20he%20was%20careful%20about%20having%20an%20engineering%20and%20management%20balance%20on%20the%20board%20because%20it%20affects%20company%20culture%20and%20how%20it%20weighs%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Altman%20brothers%20are%20intimately%20familiar%20with%20what%20can%20happen%20when%20founders%20and%20board%20members%20disagree.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESam%20Altman%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20OpenAI%20and%20Jack%20Altman's%20older%20brother%2C%20has%20been%20vocal%20about%20problems%20he%20had%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-previous-openai-board-left-him-with-complete-mess-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EChatGPT%20maker's%20board%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20year%2C%20the%20OpenAI%20chief%20said%20that%20the%20company's%20board%20left%20him%20with%20a%20%26quot%3Bcomplete%20mess%20on%20my%20hands%26quot%3B%20after%20he%20was%20reinstated%20as%20CEO%20after%20a%20brief%20ousting%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20th